00:24:20,490 --> 00:24:21,931
You affect people around you.

200
00:24:22,551 --> 00:24:26,316
And so it has a flowing outwards of effect upon the world.

201
00:24:30,161 --> 00:24:33,785
You know, you can't take upon ourselves to change somebody else.

202
00:24:33,865 --> 00:24:36,247
That's an absolutely no-no, that is.

203
00:24:36,488 --> 00:24:37,828
You know, you don't get anywhere with that.

204
00:24:38,549 --> 00:24:41,012
But when you change, you find the other person changes.

205
00:24:43,134 --> 00:24:44,696
Perhaps you've experienced that, yeah?

206
00:24:47,073 --> 00:24:50,258
I once used to talk about something I read.

207
00:24:50,917 --> 00:24:51,960
She was a journalist.

208
00:24:54,282 --> 00:24:55,224
And that's right.

209
00:24:55,244 --> 00:24:58,269
And she went to see how dolphins were trained.

210
00:24:59,550 --> 00:25:04,278
And what the trainers did was they say they were training the dolphin to jump through a hoop.

211
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:10,365
Whenever it jumped through a hoop and it did it well, it was always full of praise, right?

212
00:25:10,425 --> 00:25:11,268
Clapping or something.

